Date: 0/0/1982
Source: Collins Guide
Author: AYLING
Vol / Page: 171
Edition: 1984
Quote: <i>SAURY</i> (Needlefish)<i> Scomberesox saurus</i> ... It is similar in shape to the piper but on the saury both the upper and lower jaws are projected forward to form a sharp beak. ... [172] Sauries are often called skippers in reference to their habit of leaping clear of the water and skipping along on their tails for short distances.
